name: Quick and Easy Crab Rangoon Dip
author: Cindy Weinstein
summary: This quick and easy dip has all the flavor of fried Rangoon -- without the time and mess of frying. Won ton wrappers are baked crisp, then dipped in a creamy Asian-style sauce. They disappear fast at gatherings! The won ton wrappers may need to be baked in several batches.
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Lightly grease a large baking sheet
In a medium bowl, mix cream cheese, soy sauce, fresh ginger root, garlic, parsley and crabmeat
Cut wonton wrappers diagonally into triangles
Arrange triangles on the prepared baking sheet in a single layer
Sprinkle with paprika, increasing the amount as desired
Bake wrappers in the preheated oven until crisp and lightly browned, about 5 minutes
Pour approximately 1/2 the duck sauce over cream cheese mixture
Serve the rest with the toasted won ton wrapper triangles for dipping
